    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li>This story captures the efforts to review and analyze the expected CSV extract file for LAQ360.
	<ul>
		<li>Scope of work here would be to conclude on the specific column names and conclude on that data and its format to be inserted</li>
		<li>Envisia provides a feed with everything the Research Team needs. The CSV file provided by Anureka’s Data Team has everything they receive in Snowflake.</li>
		<li><span class="nobr"><a href="/rest/api/3/attachment/content/600892" title="HSI_AssessmentSummary_Envisia_20260601000507.xlsx attached to AS-8173" data-attachment-type="file" data-attachment-name="HSI_AssessmentSummary_Envisia_20260601000507.xlsx" data-media-services-type="file" data-media-services-id="28b87725-ee29-4585-9ffb-6e8ec2a26061" rel="noreferrer">HSI_AssessmentSummary_Envisia_20260601000507.xlsx<sup><img class="rendericon" src="/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif" height="7" width="7" align="absmiddle" alt="" border="0"/></sup></a></span></li>
		<li>Nadim followed up with Keith to see if he has file for the Research Team to share.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>AC:
	<ul>
		<li>Analyze file, document the differences needed to be made in the back end for Envisia to own scoring &amp; reporting.</li>
		<li>Confirm if Envisia’s JSON file needs to be updated.</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

